$ Oracle: V$TIMEZONE_NAMES
@ v$timezone_names

`v$timezone_names` has three columns:
  • `tzname` (for example `Europe/Zurich`)
  • `tzabbr` (the abbreviation of the timezome, for example `CET`)
  • `con_id`


{ Selecting abbreviations

  gh|oracle-patterns|/Installed/dynamic-performance-views/timezone/names/abbreviations.sql||

}

